<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Chargé in Bolivia (
                        Adam
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v11</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d289</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">289</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-06-20T14:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-06-20T14:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-20T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/6–2046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Adam</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-20T15:00:00-04:00">June 20, 1946—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>564. Had long and serious talk last night with Pinto and Paz Estenssoro. They
                    told me Aranibar has his freedom only because the President ordered it done as a
                    personal favor to me. They consider that as long as he is in his position he is
                    a threat to the stability of the Government. Under these circumstances he will
                    have to be removed to another country when the Grace vice president gets
                    here.</p>
                <p>They stated emphatically that United States press services would have to be
                    represented here by other than Bolivian citizens.</p>
                <pb facs="0369" n="351" xml:id="pg_351"/>
                <p>The Dept may wish to inform <gloss target="#t_AP1">AP</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_UP1">UP</gloss> of this situation with such recommendations as
                    seem best to it. <gloss target="#t_AP1">AP</gloss> services have been shut down
                    and none of their despatches appear in today’s <hi rend="italic">La Razón.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adam</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
